b'' b'version of ncsa mosaic for the x window system, a networked' b'information systems and world wide web browser, is hereby released:' b'' b'file://ftp.ncsa.uiuc.edu/mosaic/xmosaic-source/xmosaic-1.0.tar.z' b'.../xmosaic-binaries/xmosaic-sun.z' b'.../xmosaic-binaries/xmosaic-sgi.z' b'.../xmosaic-binaries/xmosaic-ibm.z' b'.../xmosaic-binaries/xmosaic-dec.z' b'.../xmosaic-binaries/xmosaic-alpha.z' b'.../xmosaic-diffs/xmosaic-0.13-1.0-diffs.z' b'' b'ncsa mosaic provides a consistent and easy-to-use hypermedia-based' b'interface into a wide variety of networked information sources,' b'including gopher, wais, world wide web, nntp/usenet news, techinfo,' b'ftp, local filesystems, archie, finger, hyper-g, hytelnet, texinfo,' b'telnet, tn3270, and more.' b'' b'this release of ncsa mosaic is known to compile on the following' b'platforms:' b'' b'sgi (irix b'ibm (aix b'sun (sunos with stock x11r4 and motif and gcc).' b'dec ultrix.' b'dec alpha axp (osf/1).' b'' b'documentation is available online.' b'' b'changes since include:' b'' b"o added new resource, gethostbynameisevil, for sun's that" b'coredump when gethostbyname() is called to try to find out what' b'their own names are. (command-line flag is -ghbnie.)' b'o explicitly pop down all dialog boxes when document view' b'window is closed, for window managers too dull to do so' b'themselves.' b"o better visited anchor color for non-sgi's." b'o added .hqx and .uu to list of file extensions handled like .tar files.' b"o added 'clear' button to open box, to allow more convenient" b"cut-n-paste entries of url's." b"o new resource 'autoplacewindows'; if set to false, new document" b'view windows will not be automatically positioned by the' b"program itself (but it's still up to your window manager just how" b"they're placed)." b'o command-line flags -i and -iconic now have desired effect (new' b'resource initialwindowiconic can also be used).' b'o gif-reading code is a little more bulletproof.' b'o obscure infinite loop triggered by extra space in img tag fixed.' b"o eliminated nonintuitive error message when image can't be read" b"(inlined ncsa bitmap is indication enough that something's not" b"right for authors, and readers can't do anything about bad images" b'in any case).' b'o obscure parsing bug (for constructs like <address<a' b'href=...text<a</address) fixed.' b'o fixed mysterious stupid coredump that only hits suns.' b"o fixed stupid coredump on url's like '://cbl.leeds.ac.uk/'." b"o fixed buglet in handling rlogin url's." b'o new support for solaris/sysvr4 (courtesy' b'o better support for hp-ux 8.x and 9.x (courtesy' b'o some miscellaneous portability fixes (courtesy' b'o miscellaneous bug fixes and cleanups.' b'' b'comments, questions, and bug reports should be sent to' b'provide.' b'' b'cheers,' b'marc' b'' b'--' b'--' b'marc andreessen' b'software development group' b'national center for supercomputing applications' 